%I A396635 #11 Jun 09 2026 21:11:28
%S A396635 57,96,312,480,486,2352,3720
%N A396635 Integers x such that there exist three integers 0<x<=y and 0<z<=t such that sigma(x)*psi(x)*phi(x)^2 = sigma(y)*psi(y)*phi(y)^2 = x^3 + y^3 + z^3 + t^3.
%C A396635 The numbers x, y, z and t form a sigma*psi*phi^2-cubic quadruple.
%H A396635 S. I. Dimitrov, <a href="https://github.com/Stoyan16/Sigma-psi-phi-2-cubic-quadruples/blob/main/A396635">Python program</a> (GitHub)
%e A396635 (57, 66, 39, 198) is such a quadruple because sigma(57) * psi(57) * phi(57)^2 = sigma(66) * psi(66) * phi(66)^2 = 80 * 80 * 36^2 = 144 * 144 * 20^2 = 57^3 + 66^3 + 39^3 + 198^3.
%o A396635 (Python) # See Links.
%Y A396635 Cf. A000010, A000203, A001615, A003327, A385397, A391534, A396076, A396458.
